  "prompt": "How do I rent a two wheeler in Mumbai?",
  "response": "To rent a two-wheeler in Mumbai, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Online Rental Platforms:\n- Zoomcar\n- Bounce\n- Royal Brothers\n- Drivezy\n- Wheelstreet\n\n2. Required Documents:\n- Valid driving license\n- Government-issued photo ID\n- Address proof\n- Security deposit (usually refundable)\n- Age requirement: typically 18+ years\n\n3. Rental Process:\n- Create an account on the rental platform\n- Select your preferred two-wheeler\n- Choose rental duration\n- Upload necessary documents\n- Make online payment\n- Schedule pickup or home delivery\n\n4. Offline Options:\n- Local rental shops in areas like Colaba, Bandra\n- Tourist rental points near popular locations\n- Some hotels also offer rental services\n\n5. Pricing:\n- Rates vary based on two-wheeler type\n- Daily, weekly, and monthly rental options\n- Prices range from \u20b9500-\u20b92000 per day\n\n6. Additional Tips:\n- Check vehicle condition before renting\n- Understand insurance and damage policies\n- Carry valid license and documents\n- Wear helmet for safety\n\nPro tip: Compare prices and read user reviews before finalizing your rental.",
